## 3. STAC collections

A `StacCollection` is a *catalog*, not a single raster: each item points to a COG. There
are three things you'll want to do with one.

### Discover what a STAC endpoint offers

::: {#3c1217dc .cell execution_count=12}
``` {.python .cell-code}
cols = datasets.stac_collections("https://stac.astrogeology.usgs.gov/api")
len(cols), [c["id"] for c in cols[:6]]
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=11}
```
(18,
 ['lunar_orbiter_laser_altimeter',
  'galileo_usgs_photogrammetrically_controlled_observations',
  'kaguya_terrain_camera_monoscopic_uncontrolled_observations',
  'kaguya_terrain_camera_usgs_dtms_v2_equi',
  'mro_hirise_socet_dtms',
  'kaguya_terrain_camera_stereoscopic_uncontrolled_observations'])
```
:::
:::


Any of those ids can be registered as a `StacCollection` (see §5). Three are already in the
registry:

::: {#81afd863 .cell execution_count=13}
``` {.python .cell-code}
[r.key for r in datasets.list_datasets() if r.__class__.__name__ == "StacCollection"]
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=12}
```
['usgs.mars.themis.controlled_mosaics',
 'usgs.mars.ctx.controlled_dtms',
 'usgs.moon.lola.dtms']
```
:::
:::


### Unpack a collection's contents

`items()` lists what a collection holds — no spatial filter — so you can see the products:

::: {#f1c5d44f .cell execution_count=14}
``` {.python .cell-code}
themis = datasets.mars.themis_mosaics
items = themis.items(limit=8)
[(it.id, it.cog_url.split("/")[-1]) for it in items]
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=13}
```
[('mc29_eridania_nir', 'mc29_eridania_nir.tif'),
 ('mc29_eridania_dir', 'mc29_eridania_dir.tif'),
 ('mc28_hellas_nir', 'mc28_hellas_nir.tif'),
 ('mc28_hellas_dir', 'mc28_hellas_dir.tif'),
 ('mc27_noachis_nir', 'mc27_noachis_nir.tif'),
 ('mc27_noachis_dir', 'mc27_noachis_dir.tif'),
 ('mc26_argyre_nir', 'mc26_argyre_nir.tif'),
 ('mc26_argyre_dir', 'mc26_argyre_dir.tif')]
```
:::
:::


### Search by location

When you *do* have a place in mind, `at(lon, lat)` / `search(bbox=…)` return the items
covering it:

::: {#fdeb42c6 .cell execution_count=15}
``` {.python .cell-code}
here = themis.at(lon=-90, lat=-30)      # items covering the point
[it.id for it in here]
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=14}
```
['mc17_phoenicis_lacus_nir', 'mc17_phoenicis_lacus_dir']
```
:::
:::


### Read a window from an item

A `StacItem` reads exactly like a `RemoteRaster`:

::: {#6ce980ab .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
tile = themis.at(lon=-90, lat=-30, limit=1)[0]
tile.read_window(-90, -30, 0.3)
```

